comment:
Haven't seen good English translations yet. So there is my attempt focused on meaning, not the rhymes.

x2
Wh wh wh wherever I am I will not forget home
If you want, you can spin me around like hair curls
I will find my home yard with my eyes closed
Because wherever I am I will not forget home

Wherever (I'm)Skofka is in foreign lands
I will return home through roads and fields
It hurts when you see hometown lighthouse in the distance
And you want to swim across the sea, but it's not clear how to do it

Home smells like cherry pies from the brick oven
I dreamed how I used headlights to light up the night
And watched how grandma and grandpa twisted kalachi* in the house
I wish I could pat grandpa on the shoulder right now

x2
Wh wh wh wherever I am I will not forget home
If you want, you can spin me around like hair curls
I will find my home yard with my eyes closed
Because wherever I am I will not forget home

The door squeaks
Mom's at home
Flowers on the table
Table, dinner
Hearty mom's soup
Not enough salt for dad
Quickly happily carry
Mom's soup

And again bright night in me in Kalush** was ablaze
Told me that my home yard was gone
Generations changed, walls remembered
How a child wrote the names for ages
And again bright night, but strolled without me now
And, maybe, someday I wouldn't regret
The past, that was flying away, like a raven
And I'm at home saving my nostalgia

I will come to you
Enter drunk at night
Even if you are not in sight
Even if the road is covered in snow I won't lose the track

x2
Wh wh wh wherever I am I will not forget home
If you want, you can spin me around like hair curls
I will find my home yard with my eyes closed
Because wherever I am I will not forget home

*kalachi - plural form of kalach -  twisted and circle shaped bread
** I think it's a bit of word play here since band name matches front man hometown -  can be read like ("in me/at Kalush")
